<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;display:block;"><strong style="color:rgb(69, 69, 69)"><font size="3">Actively looking to hire CS and EE PhD students in the area of software systems.<br /><br />If you are interested please send an email with your CV to:<br />first_name (dot) last_name (at) columbia (dot) edu</font></strong><br /><br /><font size="3"><font color="#454545">I am an associate professor of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science (jointly affiliated) at Columbia University, and a member of Columbia's </font>Data Science Institute<font color="#454545">. I have broad research interests in software systems and security.</font><br /><br /><font color="#454545">Previously I was the Senior Vice President of Email Protection at Barracuda Network, where I was the co-GM of the $200M email security and archiving business, with a team of 100 engineers and product managers. I was fortunate to take part in building two successful products, (</font><a href="https://www.barracuda.com/products/sentinel" target="_blank" title="">Sentinel</a><font color="#454545"> and </font><a href="https://www.barracuda.com/forensics" target="_blank" title="">Forensics</a><font color="#454545">). I</font></font><font size="3"><span style="color:rgb(69, 69, 69)"> joined Barracuda via the acquisition of the startup I founded during my PhD, Sookasa, where I was the CEO and co-founder. </span><br /><br /><span style="color:rgb(69, 69, 69)">I completed my PhD at Stanford University under </span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mendel_Rosenblum" title="">Mendel Rosenblum</a><span style="color:rgb(69, 69, 69)"> and </span><a href="http://www.stanford.edu/~skatti/" title="">Sachin Katti</a>, focusing on distributed storage systems<span style="color:rgb(69, 69, 69)">. My research was adopted in commercial storage systems of several companies, including <a href="https://www.usenix.org/system/files/fast21-pan.pdf" target="_blank" title="">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://docs.tibco.com/pub/as/3.5.0/doc/html/GUID-DF84A511-5D92-45C2-AEC3-9FF48F5C75BD.html" target="_blank" title="">Tibco</a>, <a href="https://dataworkssummit.com/barcelona-2019/session/losing-data-the-in-a-safe-way-advanced-replication-strategies-in-apache-hadoop-ozone/" target="_blank" title="">Hortonworks</a> and <a href="https://git.lukas-craft.de/root/cockroach/commit/844d7517af3dd352caf6bbe444705564c773d58b" target="_blank" title="">Rubrik</a>, and was recognized by best paper awards in <a href="https://www.usenix.org/conference/osdi22/presentation/zhong" target="_blank" title="">OSDI</a>, <a href="https://www.usenix.org/conference/usenixsecurity19/presentation/ho" target="_blank" title="">UseSec</a>, <a href="https://www.cidrdb.org/cidr2024/papers/p4-eldeeb.pdf" target="_blank" title="">CIDR</a> and <a href="https://www.usenix.org/conference/atc13/technical-sessions/presentation/cidon" target="_blank" title="">ATC</a>, and by the NSF CAREER and ARO's young investigator awards. I obtained a PhD and MS in Electrical Engineering from Stanford and BS in Computer and Software Engineering from the Technion.</span></font><br /><br /><span style="color:rgb(69, 69, 69)"><font size="3">Link to full <strong><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/wmtnlwjpi9pkle9/asaf_cidon_cv_website.pdf?dl=0" target="_blank" title="">CV</a></strong>.<br /><br />&#8203;Office: MUDD 1324, Columbia University</font></span>&#8203;</div>
